## 6. ECO / SUSTAINABILITY (5% exam)

- [ ] **UN SDGs** — 17 goals, set 2015, target 2030 (poverty, education, health, equality, clean energy, sustainable cities, climate…).
- [ ] **Goal 11** — Sustainable Cities & Communities; central to smart cities (urban population +1.5bn by 2030).
- [ ] **Mapping SDGs to a project** — pick relevant SDGs and reflect on positive AND negative external effects (not all 17).
- [ ] **Principle of public responsibility** — business and society interpenetrate, so decisions must weigh public/environmental consequences (Preston & Post 1975).
- [ ] **CSR** — context-specific actions taking stakeholder expectations and the triple bottom line into account; beyond narrow economic/legal requirements.
- [ ] **Triple bottom line** — economic, social, environmental performance (not just financial).
- [ ] **Green computing** — efficient, eco-friendly computing reducing both IT cost and environmental impact (virtualization, cloud, server consolidation, e-waste, energy reduction).
- [ ] **Herath et al. (2019) reframing** — green/CSR investment is profit-driven CSR (a win-win), not pure cost.
- [ ] **CSR as a real option** — value green investment as NPV + flexibility value (waiting for info, e.g. carbon-tax uncertainty), via Bayesian updating — not plain NPV.

