## 7. GOVERNANCE (5% exam)

- [ ] **IT governance** — high-level management/systems ensuring IT investments contribute to the business and don't waste resources (Ward & Daniel 2012).
- [ ] **IT project** — single deliverable; narrow time/cost/quality success; finite.
- [ ] **IT programme** — set of interrelated projects implementing a strategic initiative; benefits-based success; multi-year; run via PMO.
- [ ] **IT portfolio** — entirety of an org's IT investments (all projects + programmes); select & prioritise for best benefit; enduring; run by CFO-type controller.
- [ ] **Project → programme → portfolio** — progression from single deliverable to strategic initiative to whole investment landscape.
- [ ] **Programme management defined** — high-level long-term planning/supervising to assure benefits; accounts for superordinate goal, dependencies, schedule, costs/benefits/risks.
- [ ] **Lycett et al. (2004) programme goals** — efficiency/effectiveness goals (coordination, dependency mgmt, resource use, knowledge transfer, visibility) + business-focus goals (coherent communication, project definition, alignment with strategy).
- [ ] **Programme delivery issues** — keeping motivation alive, staying on track, reallocating/prioritising resources, inter-project communication.
- [ ] **Strategic Grid (Ward & Peppard 2002 / McFarlan 1983)** — 2×2 classifying investments by business contribution.
- [ ] **Strategic quadrant** — applications critical to sustaining future business strategy → invest/prioritise.
- [ ] **High Potential quadrant** — may be important to future success (uncertain) → experiment/pilot, expand or drop (real-options home).
- [ ] **Key Operational quadrant** — applications the org currently depends on → maintain/protect.
- [ ] **Support quadrant** — valuable but not critical → minimise cost.
- [ ] **Resource Allocation Matrix (Earl 2003)** — 2×2 of short/long term × pursuing opportunities/meeting obligations; cells: agile action, business transformation, firefighting, platform construction. *(Different tool from the Strategic Grid — recognise it.)*
- [ ] **Governance + portfolio management** — selecting/prioritising/monitoring all investments, linking each back to drivers and strategy.

